
[1]achor

   A'CHOR, n. [Gr., sordes capitis.]

   1. The scald head, a disease forming scaly eruptions, supposed to be a
   critical evacuation of acrimonious humors; a species of herpes.

   2. In mythology, the God of flies, said to have been worshipped by the
   Cyreneans, to avoid being vexed by those insects.
